hange Birthday<\/h3>\n\nIf you cannot change your birthday directly, your next best option is reaching out to Roblox Customer Support. Here’s what to do:\n\n- Go to the Roblox Support page.\n- Fill out the contact form, selecting “Account Issues” as the topic.\n- Provide your username, email address associated with the account, and a detailed explanation of why you need to change your birthday.\n- Be honest and clear about the reason, such as an error during sign-up or parental request.\n\nRoblox Support will review your request and may ask for proof of age or identity verification. Keep in mind that support responses can take some time, and there’s no guarantee the birthday will be changed. However, this is the official channel for making corrections in special cases.\n\n<h2>What to Do If You Can’t Change Your Birthday<\/h2>\n\nSometimes, despite your best efforts, Roblox won’t allow you to update your birthdate. In these cases, there are alternative options to consider.\n\n<h3>Create a New Roblox Account<\/h3>\n\nIf your current account’s birthday is incorrect and locked, and changing it through support isn’t feasible, you might consider creating a new account with the correct birthdate. While this means losing progress, friends, and purchases on your old account, it ensures your profile reflects accurate information and the appropriate safety settings apply.\n\n<h3>Adjust Parental Controls and Privacy Settings<\/h3>\n\nIf your birthday affects your privacy settings, parents can still manage and customize controls through the Roblox parental dashboard. This way, even if the birthday is off, you can ensure the account has appropriate restrictions and safe chat settings.\n\n<h2>Tips for Managing Your Roblox Account Safely<\/h2>\n\nBeyond just managing your birthday, maintaining your Roblox account securely is essential. Here are some useful tips:\n\n- Double-check your birthday when creating an account to avoid future issues.\n- Use a strong, unique password and ena